issue.title: Unlogged checkin action post updating the username of an asset through the CSV import

labels.name: :woman_technologist: ready for dev
labels.description: These issues are ready for someone to work on them - take your pick!

issue.body:
### Debug mode

- [X] I have enabled debug mode
- [X] I have read [checked the Common Issues page](https://snipe-it.readme.io/docs/common-issues)

### Describe the bug

I tried to update the user of an asset through the CSV importer by specifying a new username. The asset got successfully assigned to this new user, but on the history tab the checkin action wasn't logged. Only the the checkout action. As a result, we have the count of checkouts greater than the count of checkins by a margin of 2. (it should be logically only 1)

### Reproduction steps

1. Prepare the update template.
2. Specify the a new username for an asset that is already checked out to a user.
3. Upload the data through the CSV importer by checking "Update Existing Values?:" checkbox
4. Refer to the asset's history tab.


### Expected behavior

The history should have contained an action of checkin from the former user before the action of checkout for the new user.

### Screenshots

![image](https://github.com/snipe/snipe-it/assets/89049334/7f8686da-6e53-4c16-9c7d-060cf676bed1)


### Snipe-IT Version

v6.0.13 build 8923 (g30f4af3ac)

8.1.12

Windows

Brave

You can add custom settings if needed to overwrite the defaults in the SAML library. But as long as the etntiy ID matches (http or https) in the IdP that doesn't matter. It can even be a custom URN instead.

```
security.authnRequestsSigned=true
security.wantAssertionsEncrypted=true
security.wantAssertionsSigned=true
```

Other values are defined [here](https://github.com/SAML-Toolkits/php-saml#settings).

comment.body:
I can't reproduce this. Stood up a brand new setup, filled-out those fields with proper values, and I'm able to upload files just fine, that snipe-it is then able to access.

Couple of ideas:
1) can you try this using the aws cli, using those credentials, from that server, and see what happens?
2) sniff your network using ngrep, or similar, on the server, searching for outbound connections, and see what URLs you're trying to access? @snipe is absolutely correct: Timeout errors speak to a network issue -- either a bad name sending you to an address that doesn't respond, or some other kind of jank.  IS your APP_URL correct?

Also, what environment are you running in?  How permissive are the network rules _really_?

pull_request.title: Fixed FD-38641 - Bulk asset edit unable to update model_id, misc other bugs
pull_request.body: A customer in our [Discord channel](https://discord.gg/yZFtShAcKk) discovered a bug where he was having problems updating the model of assets that had custom fields. Once I went down that rabbit hole, I found a few more potential optimizations with some refactoring. Since I was in there, I did a little extra work, namely: - making the meta log output nicer (God I hate JavaScript) - adding a "unique" icon to the custom fields page so you can easily see which fields require unique constraints - fixed the checkbox/radio button display - I had missed them when we moved away from iCheck so I hadn't realized they looked so weird - Added some new custom fields seeders so we have a few more examples to make testing this easier - Fixed #13774 (I think) ### Bulk Update https://github.com/snipe/snipe-it/assets/197404/2a236731-52e9-4eea-8e6f-6a66c65f1369 ### Unique indicator https://github.com/snipe/snipe-it/assets/197404/260d022a-54d1-4366-9209-6568637085bf ### Nicer changelog ### Next Up I'd still like to continue down the refactor path and see if we can't make that a less chonk set of queries. It's kinda slow right now, and a lot of them are repeats. Some of this will be from the validation where we're checking to make sure that the location, etc actually exists in the database (which I know we have all pontificated on solutions for) but there are also just kind of a bunch we could probably tighten up. I'd also like to better handle #13798 - we do this already for some fields but not all. It's going to be annoying, but it will be less confusing. (Basically, right now, you can't blank out a lot of the fields - they just default to whatever they were before unless you submit *something*.)

issue.title: Labels Are Not Generated The Correct Size
issue.body:
#### Please confirm you have done the following before posting your bug report:

- [X] I have enabled debug mode 
- [X] I have read [checked the Common Issues page](https://snipe-it.readme.io/docs/common-issues)

**Describe the bug**
When we print labels we have a label sheet that is a 48 page grid of labels (4 by 12) that can be run through a regular printer. I have configured Snipe IT with the correct dimensions for the labels. When printing them they are either too small or too big, along with the margins being off for where they should be located.

I have tried changing the margin settings in Google Chrome to either match the label margins or setting it to 0 to see if Snipe will sort out the margins, but none of them work.

The labels are Avery brand and are code: L4778

**To Reproduce**
1. Go to label settings
2. Adjust all the margins as per the specifications of the labels
3. Select 48 devices and click generate labels
4. The produced labels will not be the correct size when printed

Labels are printed with the correct margins so they match the label positions

issue.title: Changes to Label settings seem to be ignored
issue.body:
#### Please confirm you have done the following before posting your bug report:

- [no] I have enabled debug mode 
- [x] I have read [checked the Common Issues page](https://snipe-it.readme.io/docs/common-issues)

**Describe the bug**
Changing e.g. Font Size in the Label Settings is written to Database (table: settings, field: labels_fontsize), but on next open of the Labels Settings page still shows the old/default values (in our case 9pts, although we set it to 8pts).
Printing also shows no change in FontSize.

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1. Go to 'Admin -> Labels'
2. Change Font Size to (e.g.) '8pts'  (from the 9pts before)
3. Click "Save"
4. Reload the 'Labels Settings' page and see the old values.

**Expected behavior**
Changed label settings should be correctly represented the next time the Label settings page is opened. (especially when it is written to DB)

nope

nope

nope
